The paper also involves the study of symmetric Boolean functions and circuit classes, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of $\#$SAT algorithms also relates to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents new lower bounds against specific circuit classes, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
